<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TCV53">
<l>mōṭiyōṭi laccaiyāya cāpameyti mukkaṇāṉ</l>
<l>kūṭucēṉai makkaḷōṭu koṇṭumaṇṭi veñcamat</l>
<l>tōṭavāṇa ṉāyiraṅ karaṅkaḻitta vātimāl</l>
<l>pīṭukōyil kūṭunīra raṅkameṉṟa pēratē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Raṅgam with River [Kāverī] is the name of the great Temple of the primeval Māl</l>
<l rend="indent">who cut off Bāṇa’s thousand arms,</l>
<l>as the three-eyed [Śiva], who had obtained a shameful curse, along with Durgā,</l>
<l>took the army that had come together with [his] people</l>
<l>and ran rushingly away from the battle.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
